      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-8">Last updated: December 2025</p>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-6">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Overview</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            MyBookShelf is a personal book tracking application. We are committed to protecting your privacy
            and being transparent about how we handle your data. This policy explains what information we
            collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data We Collect</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">We collect only the data necessary to provide the service:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><strong>Account information:</strong> Email address and password (encrypted)</li>
            <li><strong>Book data:</strong> Books you add, including titles, authors, ISBNs, covers, genres, ratings, and reading dates</li>
            <li><strong>Organisation data:</strong> Custom genres and series you create</li>
            <li><strong>Preferences:</strong> Display settings and widget configurations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How We Store Your Data</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">Your data is stored securely using Google Firebase:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Firebase Authentication handles login securely</li>
            <li><strong>Database:</strong> Cloud Firestore stores your books and settings</li>
            <li><strong>Location:</strong> Data is stored on Google Cloud servers</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-3">
            We also use your browser's local storage to cache data for faster loading and offline access.
            This cached data never leaves your device and can be cleared at any time from Settings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What We Don't Do</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><strong>No tracking:</strong> We don't use analytics, cookies, or tracking pixels</li>
            <li><strong>No advertising:</strong> We don't show ads or sell your data to advertisers</li>
            <li><strong>No third-party sharing:</strong> Your data is never shared with or sold to third parties</li>
            <li><strong>No profiling:</strong> We don't build profiles or analyse your reading habits for commercial purposes</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">External Services</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
            When you search for books or scan barcodes, we query these external APIs to find book information:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><strong>Google Books API:</strong> For book metadata and cover images</li>
            <li><strong>Open Library API:</strong> As a fallback for additional book data</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mt-3">
            These queries include only the ISBN or search terms you enter, not your personal information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">You have full control over your data:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> View all your data within the app at any time</li>
            <li><strong>Export:</strong> Download all your data as a JSON file from Settings</li>
            <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Permanently delete your account and all associated data from Settings</li>
            <li><strong>Clear cache:</strong> Remove locally stored data from your browser</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Your data is retained for as long as you have an account. When you delete your account,
            all your data is permanently removed from our servers. Local cached data is cleared
            when you sign out or clear your browser data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Security</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            We take security seriously. Your password is never stored in plain text. All data
            transmission uses HTTPS encryption. Firebase provides enterprise-grade security
            for authentication and data storage.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected
            on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this
            policy periodically.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy or how your data is handled,
            please reach out through the app's feedback channels.
          </p>
        </section>
